    "Emotion elicitation methodsMany emotion elicitation methods have been developed to elicit target emotions.",
    "These methods can be divided into two categories as passive and active [93].",
    "Passive methods use stimuli such as images, film clips, and music while active methods use social or dyadic interactions with a realistic scenario in a naturalistic context [93].",
    "Some studies use a single stimulus to trigger emotion, but some others use some social scenario rather than one stimulus.",
    "Some researchers also report that using more than Fig. 13 Emotion models one stimulus is more effective [31]."
  ],
